page.title: 08Blockley clubs
page.content: We went to Loraine to interview her about the Domesday project. We asked her some questions about the Guides. She first started Guides when she was asked because someone was ill.Then someone asked her to join so she joined . She has been doing Brownies for 7 years but she is doing Guides now. She has been running Guides for 6 months. We asked her how many girls were in the Guides. She said that there were 7.It is run on a Monday from 6.00 to 7.00 p.m. Then we interviewed Mr Gillett. He helps run the scouts.There are eight boys in the scouts and he has been running the scouts for 3 years.They start scouts on Friday from 7.3o to 9.30 p.m.in the Jubilee Youth Centre.
